# Xcode

## User settings
xcuserdata/

## Obj-C/Swift specific
*.hmap

## App packaging
*.ipa
*.dSYM.zip
*.dSYM

## Playgrounds
timeline.xctimeline
playground.xcworkspace

# Swift Package Manager — Xcode auto-generates .swiftpm; not needed unless a
# package configuration file exists.
.build/

# Carthage
Carthage/Build/

# fastlane — don't store generated screenshots/reports in git.
fastlane/report.xml
fastlane/Preview.html
fastlane/screenshots/**/*.png
fastlane/test_output

# macOS
.DS_Store

# Generated analysis output (graphify, etc.)
graphify-out/

# GitNexus knowledge-graph index — local-only, no network calls. Regenerate
# with `gitnexus analyze`. See docs/TOOLING.md.
.gitnexus/

# Claude Code local state
.claude/worktrees/
.claude/settings.local.json

# Secrets — never committed. See docs/ENVIRONMENT.md.
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Private notes: NOTES.md is public/committed; NOTES.local.md is personal and
# machine-specific and must never be committed. See NOTES.md.
NOTES.local.md

# Claude/agent session logs — local development history, not shipped project
# source. See CLAUDE.md's "Session logs" section.
sessions/

# task-observer skill-improvement observation log — same category as
# sessions/: local agent working state, not project source.
skill-observations/

# Agent scratch space and local logs.
tmp/*
logs/*

# website/ (Astro build — Node tooling, build output)
website/node_modules/
website/dist/
website/.astro/

# Impeccable skill — local/generated state, not project source.
# (.impeccable/design.json and .impeccable/live/config.json ARE committed —
# see .agents/skills/impeccable/reference/document.md and live.md.)
# `**/` matches at any depth: impeccable roots `.impeccable/` at cwd absent a
# monorepo marker, so invoking it from a subdirectory creates a stray. Repo
# root is the only supported root — see docs/TOOLING.md.
**/.impeccable/hook.cache.json
**/.impeccable/hook.pending.json
**/.impeccable/config.local.json
**/.impeccable/critique/
**/.impeccable/live/server.json
**/.impeccable/live/sessions/
**/.impeccable/live/previews/
**/.impeccable/live/annotations/
**/.impeccable/live/cache/
**/.impeccable/live/manual-edit-apply-transaction.json
**/.impeccable/live/manual-edit-events.jsonl
**/.impeccable/live/manual-edit-evidence/
**/.impeccable/live/pending-manual-edits.json
**/.impeccable/live/deferred-svelte-component-accepts.json
.impeccable-live.json
.impeccable-live/
node_modules/.impeccable-live/
src/lib/impeccable/ImpeccableLiveRoot.svelte
src/lib/impeccable/__runtime.js
src/lib/impeccable/[0-9a-f]*/

# GAPS.md doubles as an attacker checklist if this repo goes public — keep it
# local. Already tracked since the initial commit: this only blocks future
# re-adds (untracking needs `git rm --cached`; purging history needs a
# rewrite, e.g. git filter-repo — destructive, requires explicit sign-off).
GAPS.md

# Same reasoning as GAPS.md: keep specific-findings docs local so they can't
# double as an attacker checklist. Process docs (README, GOVERNANCE,
# AGENT-GUIDE, scripts/, templates/, markdownlint config) stay tracked.
# `security/THREAT-MODEL.md` and the audits/general/2026*.md reports are
# already tracked; same untrack/history caveat as GAPS.md applies.
security/THREAT-MODEL.md
audits/**
!audits/README.md
!audits/GOVERNANCE.md
!audits/AGENT-GUIDE.md
!audits/scripts/
!audits/scripts/**
!audits/templates/
!audits/templates/**
!audits/.markdownlint.jsonc

# docs/planning/ — original research/strategy series, kept local per explicit
# request. Already tracked (initial commit): this only stops future re-adds,
# not a history purge (needs git filter-repo — destructive, needs sign-off).
docs/planning/
.gstack/

# BMAD installer-managed personal config — "Holds install answers scoped to
# YOU personally" (see the file's own header). _bmad/custom/.gitignore
# already covers _bmad/custom/*.user.toml; this catches the root-level one
# (_bmad/config.user.toml) and any future nested copies under one rule.
_bmad/**/*.user.toml

# _bmad/ itself (module core, scripts, config) is tracked — same category as
# the already-tracked .claude/skills/bmad-*. _bmad-output/ is BMAD's
# generated planning/implementation artifact scratch space (regenerable,
# session-specific); keep it local like graphify-out/ and .gitnexus/ above.
_bmad-output/
